definition.value: A dissolution vessel identifier is an identifier that identifies some dissolution vessel. [Allotrope]
A bath identifier is an identifier that identifies some bath. [Allotrope]
A sampling time is an elapsed time at which a sample was taken from a process measured from the start of that process. [Allotrope]
A suitability calculations enabled setting is a data processing setting that indicates if system suitability results are to be calculated. [Allotrope]
An unknown suitability calculations enabled setting is a data processing setting that indicates if system suitability results are to be calculated for unknowns. [Allotrope]
A suitability pharmacopoeia setting is a data processing setting that indicates which pharmacopoeia calculation methods are to be used. [Allotrope]

label.value: half height multiplier plate count setting (USP)

definition.value: A half height multiplier plate count setting (USP) is a data processing setting that indicates at which peak height the USP plate count should be calculated. [Allotrope]
A half height multiplier resolution setting (USP) is a data processing setting that indicates at which peak height the USP resolution should be calculated. [Allotrope]

label.value: signal to noise calculation enabled setting

definition.value: A signal to noise calculation enabled setting is a data processing setting that indicates if signal to noise results are to be calculated. [Allotrope]
A blank injection noise calculation setting is a data processing setting that indicates that a blank injection is to be used for calculating baseline noise. [Allotrope]

label.value: half height multiplier signal to noise setting (USP)

definition.value: A half height multiplier signal to noise setting (USP) is a data processing setting that indicates the half height multiplier that is to be used in determining the baseline region for calculating noise in USP S/N calculations. [Allotrope]

label.value: half height multiplier signal to noise setting (EP)

definition.value: A half height multiplier signal to noise setting (EP) is a data processing setting that indicates the half height multiplier that is to be used in determining the baseline region for calculating noise in EP S/N calculations. [Allotrope]

label.value: half height multiplier signal to noise setting (JP)

definition.value: A half height multiplier signal to noise setting (JP) is a data processing setting that indicates the half height multiplier that is to be used in determining the baseline region for calculating noise in JP S/N calculations. [Allotrope]
A noise type is a classification datum that classifies the type of noise being measured. [Allotrope]

label.value: baseline noise minimum runtime percentage setting

definition.value: A baseline noise minimum runtime percentage setting is a data processing setting that indicates the minimal duration for calculating the baseline noise as a percentage of the run time. [Allotrope]
A maximum allowable noise setting is a data processing setting that indicates the maximum allowed noise value for measured noise in order for a run to be deemed valid. [Allotrope]
A maximum allowable baseline drift setting is a data processing setting that indicates the maximum allowed drift value for measured signal in order for a run to be deemed valid. [Allotrope]
A baseline noise minimum duration setting is a data processing setting that indicates the minimum duration that can be used to measure the baseline noise. [Allotrope]
A method version is a version number that identifies a method. [Allotrope]
A dispensing duration is a duration that indicates the time taken for a material to be dispensed. [Allotrope]
A dispensed volume is a volume (datum) that quantifies the volume of material that was dispensed. [Allotrope]
A torque is a quality quantification facet that quantifies some torque. [Allotrope]
A rotational speed is a quality quantification facet that quantifies some rotational speed. [Allotrope]
A location identifier is an identifier that identifies some location or site. [Allotrope]
A plate reader aggregate document is a document that aggregates plate reader documents. [Allotrope]
A plate reader document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some plate reader run. [Allotrope]
A foam height aggregate document is a document that aggregates foam height documents. [Allotrope]
A foam height document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some foam height run. [Allotrope]
A foam qualification aggregate document is a document that aggregates foam qualification documents. [Allotrope]
A foam qualification document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some foam qualification run. [Allotrope]
A gloss aggregate document is a document that aggregates gloss documents. [Allotrope]
A gloss document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some gloss run. [Allotrope]
A hot tack aggregate document is a document that aggregates hot tack documents. [Allotrope]
A hot tack document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some hot tack run. [Allotrope]
A tensile test aggregate document is a document that aggregates tensile test documents. [Allotrope]
A tensile test document is a document that encompasses the information associated with some tensile test run. [Allotrope]
A mass spectrum data cube is a data cube that is a representation of a mass spectrum. [Allotrope]
A custom information aggregate document is a document that aggregates custom information documents. [Allotrope]
A cell counting aggregate document is a document that aggregates cell counting documents. [Allotrope]
A cell counting document is a document that encompasses the information associated with a cell counting run. [Allotrope]
An illumination setting is a setting that specifies the intensity of some illumination. [Allotrope]
An exposure duration setting is a setting that specifies the duration of some exposure. [Allotrope]
A minimum cell diameter setting is a data processing setting that specifies the minimum diameter used to identify a cell in a cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
A maximum cell diameter setting is a data processing setting that specifies the maximum diameter used to identify a cell in a cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
Dead cell density is a cell counter result data that quantifies the number density of the dead cells in the sample in the cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
Average dead cell diameter is a cell counter result data that states the average diameter of the dead cells measured. [Allotrope]
An average total cell circularity is a cell counter result datum that quantifies the circularity of all cells in a cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
An average viable cell circularity is a cell counter result datum that quantifies the circularity of all viable cells in a cell counting assay. [Allotrope]
An image aggregate document is a document that aggregates image documents. [Allotrope]
A fluorescent tag setting is a setting that specifies the fluorescent tag being targeted. [Allotrope]
